  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Pre-school Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Plan and deliver engaging lessons aligned with the school’s curriculum, specializing in Cookery, Art, and outdoor activities. Communicate progress effectively to parents and contribute to the school’s educational objectives through collaborative teamwork.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design and implement lesson plans that align with the school’s curriculum and programme objectives</li><li>Deliver Cookery lessons that develop practical skills and creativity in students</li><li>Conduct Art lessons that foster artistic expression and skill development</li><li>Lead outdoor activities that promote physical engagement and experiential learning</li><li>Evaluate lessons regularly to assess student progress and improve teaching effectiveness</li><li>Provide weekly photo updates to parents to communicate student participation and achievements</li><li>Collaborate with colleagues and perform additional duties as assigned by the Principal</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hold an Advance Certificate in Early Years (ACEY), Diploma in Early Childhood Care and Education-Teaching (DECCE-T), or Diploma in Preschool Teaching</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Demonstrate fluency in English to facilitate clear communication with students and parents</li><li>Exhibit teamwork skills combined with passion and creativity to enhance the learning environment</li></ul>",
